## Plan Summary

Here's what I found and what needs to change:

### Codebase overview
- **`src/routes.ts`** — the only file to modify. `GET /users` currently does `res.json(users)`.
- **`src/data.ts`** — 15 hardcoded in-memory users, no DB layer.
- **`src/types.ts`** — `User` interface (`id`, `name`, `email`, `role`).
- **`tests/routes.test.ts`** — Vitest + Supertest tests already written for the paginated shape — they're just failing right now.

### The one change needed (`src/routes.ts`)

Replace the flat `res.json(users)` handler with:

```typescript
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  const page  = parseInt(req.query.page  as string, 10) || 1;
  const limit = parseInt(req.query.limit as string, 10) || 10;

  const total      = users.length;
  const totalPages = Math.ceil(total / limit);
  const start      = (page - 1) * limit;
  const data       = users.slice(start, start + limit);

  res.json({
    data,
    pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages },
  });
});
```

- Defaults handled by `|| 1` / `|| 10` when query params are absent.
- `slice()` past the end of the array naturally returns `[]` — no special out-of-range guard needed.
- `GET /users/:id` is untouched.

All 6 tests (4 pagination + 2 single-user) will pass after this single edit.
